  "original_title": "\u0db4\u0dc5\u0dcf\u0dad\u0dca \u0db4\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0db1 \u0db6\u0dbd\u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0daf\u0dda\u0dc1\u0dc0\u0dbd \u0d9c\u0ddc\u0da9\u0db1\u0dd0\u0d9c\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dd2 \u0dc3\u0dd0\u0dbd\u0dc3\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca \u0d85\u0db1\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dad \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db8 \u0d94\u0db1\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dba\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0db8\u0dba\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Approval of building plans in local government areas online",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Mr. Prasanna Ranatunga, Minister of Urban Development and Housing, said that an online system will be introduced to approve building plans in local government areas.",
        "The minister mentioned that this system will be introduced in 337 local government institutions across the island and it is expected to be implemented in the next two months.",
        "Minister Prasanna Ranatunga said this while addressing a discussion held today (29) with the heads of Gampaha district local government bodies at the ministry's auditorium located in Setsiripaye, Battaramulla. This discussion was held with the aim of solving the problems existing at the local government level in approving the plans.",
        "In obtaining approval for the construction of buildings, the approval for land less than 9000 square feet is assigned to the concerned local government, and if the land is more than 9000 square feet or if the building is more than 5 floors, it is the responsibility of the Urban Development Authority to give approval.",
        "The heads of the local government bodies mentioned that there are various delays in getting the plans of the local government bodies approved by the Urban Development Authority, and they pointed out that some officials bring letter files to their homes, and they also pointed out that the officials do not participate in the plan approval committee of the local government bodies. gave",
        "The Minister also instructed the Urban Development Authority to take immediate action against such officials, and it was also decided to make it mandatory for the Urban Development Authority officials to participate in the planning committee."
      ],
